description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM FOR 12 MONTHS DUE TO THE NEEDS OF THE SERVICE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A new opportunity has arisen to join the Mental Health &amp; Learning Disabilities Divisional Office support team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The existing team acts as a central administration support for all senior members for the Divisional Management structure. Due to Divisional growth the team is hoping to appoint an organized and enthusiastic Divisional Administrator to work alongside the existing Divisional Secretaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will join the team in providing a comprehensive, professional and confidential administrative service to the Mental Health and Learning Disabilities Divisional Management Team, covering for Divisional Secretaries where required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will entail frequent contact with a variety of stakeholders including members of the public (patients) and senior personnel internal and external to the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate for the role will be organised, have a high level of experience working within an administrative role, the ability to manage and prioritise their own workload and excellent customer service skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 9th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alexandra Church - Divisional Office Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;alexandra.church@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
